The Managing Board addresses sustainability-related risks and opportunities of strategic and company-wide impor- tance and adopts appropriate measures. The Managing Board also approves any changes to the DEGREE sustainability framework.

The Siemens Sustainability Board (SSB) monitors and resolves Siemens’ sustainability topics, including tracking the progress of our DEGREE ambition, providing input and guidance on sustainability reporting, and acting as a catalyst for regional sustainability initiatives with the potential to scale across Siemens. The SSB is composed of representa- tives from Siemens’ businesses, countries, and Service and Governance units. The SSB meets four times per year or more frequently as needed. The SSB provides updates and recommendations to the Managing Board.